concepts/tooling-status.md:191:Another live correction from this session: some newer geometry-side sims were rightly reclassified from `canonical` to `classical_baseline` because numpy is still computing the primary objects while richer tools only check properties of those outputs. This is not a failure; it is the intended baseline layer. The problem was false classification, not baseline existence. See [[classical-baseline-vs-canonical-tool-boundary]].
