projects/leviathan-current/lev-waverun-session-receipts-2026-07-01/THREAD_B_SEED_GATE_FRESH_AUDIT.md:58:I additionally forced a real negative on the deterministic-gate side (adversarial probe, not in the shipped suite — see answer 5 / Section "Independent adversarial probe") by setting a gate check to `status: 'fail'`: the result was `status: 'blocked'`, `acceptedClaimIds: []`, confirming the deterministic gate path is a live, content-sensitive code path, not a constant.
projects/leviathan-current/lev-waverun-session-receipts-2026-07-01/THREAD_B_SEED_GATE_FRESH_AUDIT.md:60:## 4. Is `status: 'passed'` + `nextRunSeed: null` coherent, and is host-consume kept separate from the gate verdict?
projects/leviathan-current/lev-waverun-session-receipts-2026-07-01/THREAD_B_SEED_GATE_FRESH_AUDIT.md:73:const status: ClaimGateWaveRunResult['status'] = blocked ? 'blocked' : repaired ? 'passed_after_repair' : 'passed';
projects/leviathan-current/lev-waverun-session-receipts-2026-07-01/THREAD_B_SEED_GATE_FRESH_AUDIT.md:80:- **Defensible reading**: `status: 'passed'` answers "did the deterministic, locally-checkable gates accept this claim", which is true regardless of whether a host happened to consume the run. `nextRunSeed: null` separately answers "is there a host-bound chain-forward artifact", which legitimately requires an external fact (host consumption) the wave-runner cannot manufacture. Conflating the two would force every unconsumed-but-locally-valid run to read as "blocked," which is a different and arguably false claim (the claim itself is not what's blocked — only its continuation is withheld).
projects/leviathan-current/lev-waverun-session-receipts-2026-07-01/THREAD_B_SEED_GATE_FRESH_AUDIT.md:121:Reproduced by forcing a failing gate check (`status: 'fail'` on `object_binding`): result was `status: 'blocked'`, `acceptedClaimIds: []`, `withheldClaimIds: ['WITHHELD_BRANCH']`, `nextRunSeed: null`. Correct behavior, and notably this guard is checked *before* the host-consume guard, so it is doing real, independent work — the host-consume gate is not the only thing standing between an unresolved claim and a seed.
projects/leviathan-current/lev-waverun-session-receipts-2026-07-01/THREAD_B_SEED_GATE_FRESH_AUDIT.md:123:**c. `status: 'host_blocked'` with a `receiptRef` present.**
projects/leviathan-current/lev-waverun-session-receipts-2026-07-01/THREAD_B_SEED_GATE_FRESH_AUDIT.md:125:NOT REPRODUCIBLE as a leak. `'host_blocked' !== 'host_consumed'` trips the second disjunct regardless of `receiptRef`. Reproduced: `status: 'passed'` (deterministic gates still pass — correctly independent per answer 4), `nextRunSeed: null`. Correct.
projects/leviathan-current/lev-waverun-session-receipts-2026-07-01/massaudit_synthesis.md:27:Strongest evidence: the `graph_apply_chain` skeptic minted a genuine, correctly-MAC'd ledger row in process A (`apply-graph-patch`, real `graphMutationApplied: true`), then fed that same real row into a fresh `record-graph-execution` invocation (process B) and got `status: graph_patch_blocked`, `graph_execution.graph_event_untrusted`, exit 1 — reproduced twice, deterministic. Root cause independently confirmed by direct code read: `HOST_GRAPH_EVENT_TRUST_PROCESS_SECRET = randomBytes(32)` is a bare module-level constant, no file, no env, no IPC (`core/orchestration/src/proof/claim-gate-loop.ts:1208` per skeptic's own re-derived line numbers — note the lens's original citations 615-630/743-745 were stale/from a different file copy, a sourcing-hygiene defect the skeptic flagged but did not treat as refuting the finding). The `cross_process_module` lens+skeptic pair independently confirms the fix exists (`host-trust-secret.ts`, file-sealed, race-safe, genuinely tested across a real spawned OS process) but is wired into zero production call sites — three separate `randomBytes(32)` instances remain live (`claim-gate-loop.ts:76`, `proof/claim-gate-loop.ts:1208`, `claim-gate-steering-run.ts:32`). **This is availability-class, not forgery-class** — no attacker gets a free mutation; the system fails closed, but it also fails closed for the legitimate multi-step chain, which is the architecture the whole spine is meant to support.
projects/leviathan-current/lev-waverun-session-receipts-2026-07-01/THREAD_B_HOSTCONSUME_FORGERY_FIX_RECEIPT.md:90:    `handler(['wave-run', ...])` in the same process: `status:'passed'`, real `nextRunSeed`
projects/leviathan-current/lev-waverun-session-receipts-2026-07-01/THREAD_B_SEED_GATE_RECEIPT.md:28:- (repair errors already force `status: blocked` upstream, which is checked at the call site)
projects/leviathan-current/lev-waverun-session-receipts-2026-07-01/THREAD_B_SEED_GATE_RECEIPT.md:34:`ClaimGateWaveRunHostConsume { status: 'host_consumed'|'adapter_projection_only'|'host_blocked'|'absent'; receiptRef?: string }`
